texts.label: text
texts.orig: Example Actions: To create a PFD definition file, type 12 (Work with PFD definition files) on the command line on the IBM Advanced Function Printing Utilities for iSeries menu and press the Enter key.
texts.text: Example Actions: To create a PFD definition file, type 12 (Work with PFD definition files) on the command line on the IBM Advanced Function Printing Utilities for iSeries menu and press the Enter key.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: The Work with PFD Definition Files display appears to create a PFD definition file.
texts.text: The Work with PFD Definition Files display appears to create a PFD definition file.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: The library name that you used last is displayed in the Library prompt and *ALL is displayed in the File prompt.
texts.text: The library name that you used last is displayed in the Library prompt and *ALL is displayed in the File prompt.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: Example Actions: Type MYLIB in the Library prompt and press the Enter key to list PFD definition files stored in MYLIB.
texts.text: Example Actions: Type MYLIB in the Library prompt and press the Enter key to list PFD definition files stored in MYLIB.

texts.label: text
texts.orig: Note: No PFD definition file is shown because no PFD definition files are stored in MYLIB.
texts.text: Note: No PFD definition file is shown because no PFD definition files are stored in MYLIB.
